  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Aemilius Asper, The grammarian A., most likely from the late 2nd cent. 
    AD, sums up the tension between archaistic and classical tendencies of the school canon in the 2nd cent. with his 
    explanations of Terentius, Vergilius and Sallustius. In his exegesis, the interest in historical-linguistic detailed
    phenomena takes second place to textual criticism, stylistics and the comparison with Greek classics....." 
    Schmidt, Peter L. (Constance) "Aemilius Asper." Brill’s New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: 
    Hubert Cancik and , Helmuth Schneider. Brill Online, 2014. Reference. Tufts University. 18 December 2014</mads:note>
